## First Steps

```bash
uv sync
uv run pre-commit install
git add .
git add uv.lock
git commit -m "Initial project setup"
```

## Common Commands

Format code:

```bash
uv run ruff format .
```

Lint:

```bash
uv run ruff check src tests
```

Type check:

```bash
uv run mypy src tests
```

Run tests:

```bash
uv run pytest
```

Build the package:

```bash
uv build
```

## Project Layout

```text
src/{{ package_name }}/     reusable package code
tests/                      pytest tests
.github/workflows/          GitHub Actions CI
AGENTS.md                   AI assistant coding instructions
pyproject.toml              project metadata and tool configuration
uv.lock                     locked dependencies
```

## Dependencies

Use `uv add` to keep project metadata and the lockfile in sync.

Examples:

```bash
uv add requests
uv add --dev pytest-mock
```

If code in `src/` imports a package at runtime, that package belongs in base
dependencies. If a package is only used for development, add it to the dev group.

## Lockfile

This project expects `uv.lock` to be committed.

The first `uv sync` creates it. CI installs from the committed lockfile with
`uv sync --frozen`.

Dependabot is configured to open weekly PRs for uv dependency and GitHub Actions
updates. CI validates each Dependabot PR automatically.
